Ukraine May Reap 18 Million Tons of Corn, Uryadovyi Kurier Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-08-02T07:20:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/ukraine-may-reap-18-million-tons-of-corn-uryadovyi-kurier-says.html
Ukraine may harvest more than 18
million metric tons of corn this year,  Uryadovyi Kurier 
newspaper reported, citing Mykola Bezuhlyi, the country’s first
deputy agriculture minister.  Bezuhlyi sees corn yields “at least” at 5 tons a hectare
(2.47 acres), according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
